      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While your body is resilient, pushing 50,000 IU daily for a month is unnecessary overkill and risks hypercalcemia, which is what strains the kidneys. Hydration helps, but it doesn't negate the chemical overload from massive Vitamin D saturation. For maximum, yet safe, results, stick to a targeted 5,000 IU daily supplemented with a good dose of Vitamin K2 to manage calcium absorption. This combination is the gold standard for true cellular optimization.",
      "source": "target",
